For the session storage library, we are following standard Go package structure.

This is a small reusable library, not a full application, so we are keeping one package and splitting files by responsibility instead of creating many folders.

Current structure:

iva-session-storage/
  types.go          Public types
  writer.go         Main write/save workflow
  dynamodb.go       DynamoDB request helpers
  validation.go     Input validation
  errors.go         Shared errors
  writer_test.go    Writer tests
  README.md
  go.mod
  go.sum

When we add reader functionality, we will add:

  reader.go
  reader_test.go

We are avoiding folders like service/, repository/, models/, and handlers/ because those are more suitable for large applications. In Go, every folder becomes a package, so adding folders too early creates unnecessary complexity.

If the library grows significantly later, we can introduce an internal/ folder for private implementation details. For now, one package with clear file separation is simpler, readable, and maintainable.
